# Automatic variables in `Makefile`
# https://www.gnu.org/software/make/manual/html_node/Using-Variables.html

- $@ = target filename
- $< = name of first pre-requisite
- $^ = names of all pre-requisites, space separated
- $? = names of all pre-requisites newer than target, space separated

# Filename-splitting functions

- $(@D) = directory portion of $@   `/path/to/foo` => `/path/to`
- $(@F) = filename portion of $@    `/path/to/foo` => `foo`
- same pattern for $<, $^, $?, etc.

# Other

- Variable names are case-sensitive
